	<p align="center"><font class="pageHeader">~ R U L E S ~</font></p>
		
	<blockquote>All members must follow the following set of rules and guidelines and have
	the following rights.
	<ul>
		<li>When there is no Leader of The Hidden all Members have the right to elect
		one.</li>
		<li>When a Leader apoints a new Council Member all Members have the right to vote
		on this appointee before they are allowed to become a Council Member.</li>
		<li>If a Member has problems needing to be resolved they are to be brought to the
		Leader.</li>
		<li>If the problem is dealing with the Leader it is to be brought to the Council.</li>
		<li>A Member shall not intentionally Kill Steal, Ninja Loot, Train, Exploit,
		Swear excessively, or commit any other violations of Verant Interactive(tm)
		policies to any Member of The Hidden or any EverQuest Player on the penalty of
		being removed from The Hidden.</li>
		<li>Attendance for any Guild Events(Any type of Guild Meetings or Invasions) is
		mandatory if you are online. Real life comes first and all effort will be made to
		schedule events with as few conflicts as possible.</li>
		<li>All Members are expected to be active in The Hidden. This is
		defined as visiting the Guild page and, Message boards regularly, attending Guild
		Events and having a presence in game, and checking an email address provided to
		the Guild Leader regularly. Again real life comes first.</li>
		<li>All Members shall strive for the betterment of The Hidden and to aid their
		Guildmates to the best of their abilities.</li>
		<li>Members will follow orders of the Leader, or in his absense or apointment any
		Council Member.</li>
		<li>Members are expected to put effort back into the guild, those who go above what
		is needed in all aspects should be considered for the Council.</li>
	</ul>
	All Council Members must follow the above set of guidlines along with those outlined
	below.
	<ul>
		<li>In the event the Council finds fault with the Leader they have the right to
		initiate a Guild-wide vote to impeach the Leader on a set of terms they set forth.
		All Members are required to vote and simple majority rules.</li>
		<li>Council Members will be given an Officer position in game and are expected to
		to use this power with discretion and in the case when a Prospective Member is
		approved for membership it is the responsibility of the nearest Council Memeber to
		invite them.</li>
		<li>When the leader is absent the Council shall act in his stead where
		appropriate.</li>
		<li>All Council Members shall know The Hidden's policys and be prepared to answer
		questions from Guildmates and those outside of the guild.</li>
		<li>All Council Members shall have an email address easily avaible for anyone to
		contact them with.</li>
	</ul>
	The Leader, along with following the guidlines for regular Members must also follow those
	outlined below.	
	<ul>
		<li>The Leader of The Hidden shall hold the Guild Leader title in game and is
		responsible for apointing up to three members for the council and inviting them
		as Officers ingame.</li>
		<li>The Leader of The Hidden is the one Leader of the Guild and should apoint a
		council to council him on matters, it is the Leader who makes the final descision
		though.</li>
		<li>With any problems or disputes involving any Members or Council Members the
		Leader and the remaining Council should discuss the options and then execute them
		to solve the problem as quickly and fairly as possible.</li>
		<li>The Leader shall have an email address easily avaible for anyone to	contact
		him with.</li>
	</ul></blockquote>

